data.chText: 补救；弥补；掩饰…之不足
data.enText: to make sb/sth seem less bad

data.chText: 精彩的表演不足以掩盖情节的拙劣。
data.enText: The excellent acting wasn't enough to redeem a weak plot.

data.chText: 这份工作唯一的可取之处就是它的工资。
data.enText: The only redeeming feature of the job (= good thing about it) is the salary.

data.chText: 挽回影响；改变印象；维护
data.enText: to do sth to improve the opinion that people have of you, especially after you have done sth bad

data.chText: 他有机会弥补上星期犯下的错误。
data.enText: He has a chance to redeem himself after last week's mistakes.

data.chText: 拯救；救赎
data.enText: to save sb from the power of evil

data.chText: 耶稣基督来将我们从罪恶中拯救出来。
data.enText: Jesus Christ came to redeem us from sin.

data.chText: 偿清；付清
data.enText: to pay the full sum of money that you owe sb; to pay a debt

data.chText: 清偿贷款 / 按揭贷款
data.enText: to redeem a loan/mortgage

data.chText: 兑换；兑现
data.enText: to exchange sth such as shares or vouchers for money or goods

data.chText: 这抵用券在我们的任一分支机构都可以使用。
data.enText: This voucher can be redeemed at any of our branches.

data.chText: 赎回
data.enText: to get back a valuable object from sb by paying them back the money you borrowed from them in exchange for the object

data.chText: 他得以从当铺赎回他的表。
data.enText: He was able to redeem his watch from the pawnshop.

data.chText: 履行，遵守（诺言）
data.enText: to do what you have promised that you will do

data.chText: 以上各词均含拯救、挽救、营救之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to prevent sb/sth from dying, losing sth, being harmed or embarrassed.
save

data.chText: 指救、救助、挽救、拯救：
data.enText: to prevent sb/sth from dying, being harmed or destroyed or losing sth

data.chText: 医生未能把他救活。
data.enText: Doctors were unable to save him.

data.chText: 一场拯救大熊猫之使免于灭绝的运动
data.enText: a campaign to save the panda from extinction
rescue

data.chText: 指营救、援救、抢救：
data.enText: to save sb/sth from a dangerous or harmful situation

data.chText: 他们被一艘经过的游轮救起。
data.enText: They were rescued by a passing cruise ship.
bail sb out

data.chText: 尤指通过提供钱帮助某人脱离困境：
data.enText: to rescue sb/sth from a difficult situation, especially by providing money

data.chText: 如果一切都搞砸了，就别指望我来解救你。
data.enText: Don't expect me to bail you out if it all goes wrong.
redeem

data.chText: 指拯救、救赎：
data.enText: ( formal , religion ) to save sb from the power of evil

data.chText: 他是一个罪人，承蒙上主的恩宠才得以拯救。
data.enText: He was a sinner, redeemed by the grace of God.

data.chText: redeem亦用于非宗教语言中，如redeem a situation意为力挽狂澜。
data.enText: Redeem is also used in non-religious language in the phrase redeem a situation , which means to prevent a situation from being as bad as it might be.
to save/rescue/redeem sb/sth from sth
to be able/unable to save/rescue/bail out/redeem sb/sth
an attempt/effort to save/rescue/redeem sb/sth
to save/rescue/redeem a situation
to save/redeem sinners/mankind
to rescue sb/bail sb out financially

simple_means.memory_skill: red〔= re 回〕+ eem〔= em〕拿；获得 → 拿回 → 赎回

ex.chText: 律师说，她应该为所遭受的痛苦得到赔偿。
ex.enText: The lawyer said she should be compensated for the sufferings.

ex.chText: 幸存者每人得到3万美元，作为对他们所受损失的补偿。
ex.enText: Survivors were given $30,000 each to help compensate for their losses.

ex.chText: 她的聪明才智弥补了她的经验不足。
ex.enText: Her intelligence compensates for her lack of experience.

synonyms.bx: 指因使他人受到伤害、损失等而给予赔偿，也指对某事的不良影响进行弥补，常后接介词 for。

ex.enText: He felt he had atoned for his sins.

ex.chText: 他急切地想弥补自己的疏忽之过。
ex.enText: He is anxious to atone for his neglect.

synonyms.bx: 指弥补过错或赎罪，常后接介词 for。

ex.chText: 你的行为的唯一可取之处就是你没有对此否认。
ex.enText: The single redeeming feature of your behaviour is that you're not denying it.

synonyms.bx: 主要指偿还所欠债务，也指对事情进行补救。

ex.chText: 地震生还者被直升机救了出来。
ex.enText: Survivors of the earthquake were rescued by helicopter.

ex.chText: 士兵们千方百计地营救被洪水围困的当地居民。
ex.enText: The soldiers tried every possible means to rescue the local residents trapped by the flood.

synonyms.bx: 多指从危难中救出某人。

ex.chText: 基督徒认为耶稣•基督是来解救我们摆脱罪孽的。
ex.enText: Christians believe that Jesus Christ came to redeem us from sin.

synonyms.bx: 一般用作宗教用语 ，指将某人从罪恶中解救出来。

ex.chText: 一名年轻男子救起了那个溺水儿童。
ex.enText: A young man saved the child from drowning.

ex.chText: 他不知该如何挽救自己的友谊。
ex.enText: He didn't know how to save his friendship.

ex.chText: 一个团体发起了保护热带雨林的运动。
ex.enText: A group campaigned to save the rainforests.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，含义广泛，既可指营救某人使其脱离危险，也可指挽救关系、婚姻等。

tr: exchange or buy back for money
to turn in (vouchers or coupons) and receive something in exchange
restore the honor or worth of

value.def: If you redeem yourself or your reputation, you do something that makes people have a good opinion of you again after you have behaved or performed badly.

example.ex: He had realized the mistake he had made and wanted to redeem himself...
example.tran: 他已经认识到了自己的错误，想要进行弥补。

example.ex: The sole redeeming feature of your behaviour is that you're not denying it.
example.tran: 你的行为中唯一可取之处就是你没有否认错误。

value.tran: 挽回（声誉）；补偿，弥补（过错）

value.def: When something redeems an unpleasant thing or situation, it prevents it from being completely bad.

example.ex: Work is the way that people seek to redeem their lives from futility...
example.tran: 工作可以避免人们虚度生命。

example.ex: ...a long face with too prominent features that were redeemed by a fine pair of brown eyes...
example.tran: 脸部较长，五官很突出，还好一双棕色的眼睛长得恰到好处

example.ex: Does this institution have any redeeming features?
example.tran: 这个机构有什么可取之处吗？

value.def: If you redeem a debt or money that you have promised to someone, you pay money that you owe or that you promised to pay.

example.ex: The amount required to redeem the mortgage was £358,587...
example.tran: 需要偿还的抵押贷款总计358,587英镑。

example.ex: Take the voucher to your local branch of Woolworths and it will be redeemed for one toy.
example.tran: 持兑换券到当地沃尔沃斯的分店可以兑换一个玩具。

value.def: If you redeem an object that belongs to you, you get it back from someone by repaying them money that you borrowed from them, after using the object as a guarantee.

example.ex: Make sure you know exactly what you will be paying back when you plan to redeem the item.
example.tran: 务必弄清楚将来赎回物品时需要支付多少钱。

value.def: In religions such as Christianity, to redeem someone means to save them by freeing them from sin and evil.

example.ex: ...a new female spiritual force to redeem the world.
example.tran: 全新的拯救世界的女性精神力量

ex 出 + ampl 拿；获得 + e → 拿出〔好的〕来 → 作榜样 → 榜样
ex 出 + empl〔= ampl〕拿；获得 + ar 表物 → 拿出来用作例子 → 典型
exempl〔e〕举例 + ify 使 → 举例说明
ex 出 + empt 拿；获得 → 获得出去〔的权利〕→ 豁免
per 加强 + empt 拿；获得 + ory …的 → 全部都拿 → 专横的
pre 预先 + empt 拿；获得 → 先拿 → 先发制人
partsOfSpeech.d: 以先买权取得；先发制人

red + empt 拿；获得 + ion 表名词 → 赎回，买回
